reviewText:
My grandson is 3 and he LOVES Stuart Little and I was more than happy to
purchase the collection for him. It's also fun watching Hugh Laurie (he's
so diffent from his character in House)show his compassionate, loving,
parental side.
Enjoyed 1 & 2.  I was a little disappointed that 3 was a cartoon.  Kids didn't seem to mind they loved all 3.  I do find they watching 1 & 2 more often though.

Great set of movies. My 3 1/2 year old loves them. It nice to find a set of movies that doesn't really have any "scary parts" that I have to fast-forward through. Plus they're fun for adults too. I don't mind at all watching them too.
I really though I was getting the animation version.

My kid loves this movie. Thrilled to have found the bundle. Every disk works.

This was one of my sons favorite movies!  They both loved Stuart!  Stuart Little 1 and Stuart Little 2 are super cute movies!!  Stuart Little 3 is just ok (cartoon versus an actual live movie with actors).  Stuart Little is all around a great movie for little kids, especially toddlers.  We also purchased the book so that my boys could enjoy the story too as I read it to them or for when they are older to read themselves.  For $5, this triple movie series is a great add-on to a gift or holiday little something gift.
nice case to keep them in, great quality picture.

This is not the pack to get if you getting this for DVD. This pack has the 1st movie in Full Screen. If you want quality for DVD, then get the 2013 print version of 1 & 2 on a double feature. That is 5 dollars at wal-mart too by the way. Then, get the 3rd movie separately. Then you will have all 3 widescreen and cheaper than this awful package. If you decide on Blu-ray, get 1 & 2 on Blu-ray and the 3rd on DVD.

I have twin 3 1/2 year olds and one of my sons will wake up wanting to watch "the mouse".  Stewart Little 2 is on Netflix and has been eating up my download internet limit.  My sons love this little mouse so much I'm buying the box set.  I didn't know there were 3 of these movies and I have to admit it is funny and I'm looking forward to watching 2 more movies.

My five year old twin grandchildren are big fans of Stuart.  Until I bought this set, we only had one Stuart movie and were well on our way to wearing it out.  I have also found myself to be a Stuart fan after watching with the twins.  Maybe I'm just a kid at heart!

My three year old loves this!!! He has seen all the other popular things and was so bored. We remembered this
cute little show and it kept him entertained time and time again!

We originally had the first two Stuart Little DVDs, but got this for my grandson's recent birthday. I hadn't seen the third, animated, video.

He loves Stuart so much we watch at least one of these several times a week. He is always talking about Stuart.

The rest of us enjoy watching Hugh Laurie in a totally different character than House. All of the characters were well chosen, and the Stuart Little movies are great family entertainment.

I like that a lot of these movies slip in references that adults can enjoy. As many times as I have now seen all three, I still have fun!
Purchased so my grandson could see the Stuart Little movies both at my house and at home.
We have had this set for just over a year.  Well worth the money.  My 3 year old loves #3 - I'm not a fan of that one but he really enjoys it.
